BT /F2 18 Tf 54.00 692.00 Td (3. Foundations: Where Attachment Theory Comes From) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 666.50 Td (To use attachment theory well in adult life, you need to see what it actually is - and what it is not. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 651.65 Td (popular version often gets flattened into a personality test. It is more interesting and more useful than) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 636.80 Td (that.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54.00 595.95 Td (3.1 The biological core) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 573.45 Td (Attachment theory began with John Bowlby in the 1950s-60s. Working with separated and orphaned) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 558.60 Td (children after WWII, Bowlby observed that infants do not just need food and warmth - they need a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 543.75 Td (specific caregiver and reliably fall apart without one. He proposed that humans, like other mammals,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 528.90 Td (evolved an attachment system: a set of behaviors \(crying, clinging, seeking proximity\) whose) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 514.05 Td (evolutionary job is to keep the young close to a protector. This is not learned. It is hardware.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 492.20 Td (Mary Ainsworth turned Bowlby's ideas into measurable research with the Strange Situation procedure.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 477.35 Td (Toddlers were briefly separated from caregivers and observed on reunion. Three reproducible patterns) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 462.50 Td (emerged - secure, anxious-ambivalent, and avoidant - plus a later fourth \(disorganized\) added by Mary) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 447.65 Td (Main.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 425.80 Td (The leap that made the field relevant to adults came in 1987, when Cindy Hazan and Phillip Shaver) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 410.95 Td (showed that the same patterns appear in adult romantic relationships. Romantic partners function as) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 396.10 Td (attachment figures the same way caregivers do for children. The implication is uncomfortable and true:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 381.25 Td (adult love is not only about compatibility, values, or chemistry. It is also about two attachment systems) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 366.40 Td (trying to regulate each other.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54.00 325.55 Td (3.2 Why the system matters more than you think) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 303.05 Td (When the attachment system is activated - by separation, ambiguity, fear of loss, conflict - it overrides) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 288.20 Td (almost everything else. Smart people make stupid relationship choices not because they are stupid, but) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 273.35 Td (because the attachment system is older and faster than the prefrontal cortex. You cannot reason) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 258.50 Td (yourself out of it in real time. You can only build a life and a relationship that activate it less) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 243.65 Td (catastrophically.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 221.80 Td (This is why willpower-based advice \('just do not text him'\) usually fails. It tells the modern brain to win a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 206.95 Td (fight against ancient circuitry that has had millions of years of practice. The realistic move is to set up) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 192.10 Td (conditions where the attachment system is satisfied, not to pretend it is not there.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54.00 151.25 Td (3.3 The dependency paradox) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 128.75 Td (A central, counterintuitive finding: secure attachment produces more independent functioning, not less.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 113.90 Td (People with a reliably available partner take more risks, explore more, perform better, and recover from) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 99.05 Td (setbacks faster. The cultural script that says 'do not need anyone' is biologically backwards. Humans) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 84.20 Td (are wired to venture out from a base, not to operate alone.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 303.50 30.00 Td (5) Tj ET
