BT /F2 18 Tf 54.00 692.00 Td (4. The Three Styles, Properly Understood) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 666.50 Td (Most popular write-ups of attachment styles flatten them into personality cliches: anxious people are) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 651.65 Td (needy, avoidant people are cold, secure people are unicorns. That is wrong in a way that matters. Each) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 636.80 Td (style is a coherent strategy - it solves a real problem, just at a high cost.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54.00 595.95 Td (4.1 Secure \(roughly 50-55% of adults\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 573.45 Td (Core experience: closeness is safe; autonomy is safe. Conflict does not feel like a threat to the bond.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 558.60 Td (Disagreement does not flip the system into emergency.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 536.75 Td (How they actually behave: they ask for what they want, in plain language, without weaponizing it. They) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 521.90 Td (listen without immediately defending. They assume good intent until shown otherwise. They do not) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 507.05 Td (panic over delayed replies. They do not punish small distance with big withdrawal. They give partners) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 492.20 Td (the benefit of context.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 470.35 Td (What feels weird about them in early dating: their nervous system is calm, so the relationship does not) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 455.50 Td (produce the spikes that anxious or avoidant people read as 'real' chemistry. People often call secure) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 440.65 Td (partners 'boring' for the first few weeks, then realize three months later that nothing has gone wrong) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 425.80 Td (and that the calm itself is the gift. This is the most expensive misreading in dating.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 403.95 Td (Important nuance: 'secure' is not the same as 'has no issues.' A secure person can be insecure in other) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 389.10 Td (domains \(career, family, anxiety\). The label refers to the attachment dimension only.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54.00 348.25 Td (4.2 Anxious \(roughly 20% of adults\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 325.75 Td (Core experience: closeness is the goal; perceived distance is danger. The system reads ambiguity as) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 310.90 Td (rejection by default.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 289.05 Td (Internal logic, expressed honestly: 'If I do not stay vigilant about the connection, I will lose it. The cost of) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 274.20 Td (overreacting is small; the cost of missing a real loss is catastrophic.' That trade-off is not crazy. It is the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 259.35 Td (rational behavior of a system that has learned, early or repeatedly, that closeness is unreliable.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 237.50 Td (Strengths people miss: anxious individuals are often the most attuned partners in the room. They notice) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 222.65 Td (shifts in tone, body language, and emotional weather. In a calm, secure pairing, that sensitivity) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 207.80 Td (becomes warmth, not surveillance.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 185.95 Td (Costs: a never-resting threat detector is exhausting. False positives produce protest behavior \(we will) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 171.10 Td (unpack that\). Self-worth becomes hostage to partner responsiveness. Choices skew toward partners) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 156.25 Td (who trigger the system the most - which is usually the wrong partner.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54.00 115.40 Td (4.3 Avoidant \(roughly 25% of adults\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 92.90 Td (Core experience: autonomy is the goal; closeness is engulfment. The system reads emotional demand) Tj ET
BT /F1 9 Tf 303.50 30.00 Td (7) Tj ET
