BT /F2 18 Tf 54.00 692.00 Td (5. How Styles Interact: The Dynamics of Pairings) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 666.50 Td (Attachment style is not a fixed label on a person. It is a tendency that comes alive in interaction. Two) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 651.65 Td (anxious people behave differently together than an anxious paired with an avoidant. Map the pairings,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 636.80 Td (and a lot of relationship behavior stops looking mysterious.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54.00 595.95 Td (5.1 Secure + anyone) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 573.45 Td (A secure partner has a stabilizing effect across the board. With another secure, the relationship is calm) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 558.60 Td (and low-drama; conflict is resolved by talking. With an anxious partner, the secure absorbs the spikes,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 543.75 Td (responds reliably, and over time the anxious nervous system de-escalates. With an avoidant partner,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 528.90 Td (the secure does not chase, does not punish distance, and does not destabilize on small withdrawals -) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 514.05 Td (which paradoxically makes the avoidant safer to step in.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 492.20 Td (Bottom line: secure partners are not exotic. They are underweighted in dating because they generate) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 477.35 Td (fewer fireworks. The shift you can make today is to stop filtering them out as boring.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54.00 436.50 Td (5.2 Anxious + anxious) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 414.00 Td (Two threat-detecting systems pointed at each other. Often very close, very intense, with frequent) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 399.15 Td (reassurance rituals. Can work, but the relationship spends a lot of energy on the connection itself rather) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 384.30 Td (than on living. Risk: the bond becomes the entire world; outside life thins out.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54.00 343.45 Td (5.3 Avoidant + avoidant) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 320.95 Td (Two distance-keeping systems. Looks low-conflict from outside; can quietly starve emotionally. Often) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 306.10 Td (works for practical partnership \(logistics, household, kids\) but lacks the felt closeness that makes a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 291.25 Td (relationship regenerative. Risk: drift, parallel lives, low satisfaction reported only after years.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54.00 250.40 Td (5.4 Anxious + avoidant: the pattern that hurts) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 227.90 Td (This is the pairing the field talks about most because it is common, intense, and reliably miserable. It is) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 213.05 Td (worth understanding in detail because, statistically, this is the loop people get stuck in.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 191.20 Td (Why it is common: in single-person dating pools, secure people pair off earlier and more stably.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 176.35 Td (Anxious and avoidant people stay in circulation longer, so they meet each other more often. Selection) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 161.50 Td (bias, not romance.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 139.65 Td (Why it feels intense: each system pushes the other's buttons. Anxious closeness-seeking activates) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 124.80 Td (avoidant distance-seeking, which activates anxious protest, which activates more avoidant distance,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 109.95 Td (and so on. The highs of reconnection feel huge because the lows of perceived loss were huge. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 95.10 Td (brain learns to read this oscillation as 'passion'. It is not. It is intermittent reinforcement, the same) Tj ET
