BT /F2 14 Tf 54.00 647.50 Td (A. Glossary) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70.00 625.00 Td (Ģ Attachment system - an evolved emotional/behavioral system that regulates closeness with a) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70.00 610.70 Td (primary caregiver, and later with a romantic partner.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70.00 592.40 Td (Ģ Secure base - a person whose reliable availability lets you explore the world with less fear.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70.00 574.10 Td (Ģ Safe haven - a person you can return to for comfort when distressed.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70.00 555.80 Td (Ģ Activation - the state of the attachment system responding to perceived threat to closeness.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70.00 537.50 Td (Ģ Hyperactivation - the anxious strategy: turn the system up, demand contact.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70.00 519.20 Td (Ģ Deactivation - the avoidant strategy: turn the system down, suppress the need.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70.00 500.90 Td (Ģ Protest behavior - actions that try to force re-engagement when distance is perceived.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70.00 482.60 Td (Ģ Earned secure - someone who developed secure functioning later in life rather than from) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70.00 468.30 Td (childhood.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70.00 450.00 Td (Ģ Internal working model - the implicit map you carry of what closeness costs and what it gives.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 70.00 431.70 Td (Ģ Disorganized / fearful-avoidant - a mixed pattern where closeness is both wanted and feared.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54.00 394.40 Td (B. Self-assessment prompts) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 54.00 371.90 Td (Answer in writing, in your own words. The point is not to score yourself; it is to make the patterns) Tj ET
